    'month' => '01',
    'index' => 'cd258',
    'body' => 'Just a friendly reminder, most of the people on this list are digest
subscribers and when you reply to a message try to avoid quoting the entire
message or even a subsequent part.  Only include what is absolutely
required or summarize.  Here are the reasons why this is important:

TML is a busy list.  People can read the messages faster, and generally can
follow threads without having to re-read the entire message.  The only time
when this fails is when people sign on in the middle of the list.  However
they can go to the ftp site and get the previous digests to catch up.

Secondly, when people read their digests, there is a good chance that they
have just read the original message that is being quoted anyway, so it
isn\'t necessary.

Thirdly, it increases the size of the messages which slows down our mail
server and can create log jams that cause you to not get your TML in a
timely fashion.   Kinda follow this a bit.  The excess traffic causes
accounts to go over quota and then we get bounces which slows down our mail
server even more.

There are certain rules of Netiquette that should be followed on mailing
lists, at least until mailing list and email software catches up in
technology.

1.   Make sure you contribute more than you quote.  If you quote 5 lines of
text, your contribution to the thread should be at least that much if not
more text.

2.   Your contribution should be meaningful.  Avoid "Me Toos", "I agree"s,
and "You go, Girl!"s.  Humor while entertaining, can be wasteful as well.
So hold back on the sarcastic and humorous comments unless it really adds
to the thread.

3.  Keep your signatures short.  4 lines or less is recommended.  Make sure
your original content is more than your signature.  This means avoid
sending PGP keys unless you can get that signature down to 4 or 5 lines.
Your PGP key can be a simple one liner:

       For my PGP public key:  http://www.somesite.com/~me/mypgp.html

Mailing list traffic is clear channel anyway, so no need to clog up the
airways with all that encrypted stuff.

4.  Avoid attachments and styles.  Attachments get imbedded into the
digests and are annoying as heck.  This means turn off automatically
sending Vcards in IE and Netscape.  Do not send attachments.  If you are
using Eudora 4.0, IE or Netscape, do not send "Styles" to mailing lists.
What happens is that your message becomes MIME encoded with multiple copies
of the message, one plain text and one rich text, and possibly HTML.  Each
copy gets stuck into the digest and can mess up peoples ability to read
digests.

5.  If a thread\'s subject no longer matches the thread, change the subject.

6.  Try to avoid restarting topics that end up in long debates.  So no
Asteroids as Missiles type threads.

Thank you for your attention.

Rob Miracle
List Mom.

BTW:  Visit http://www.mpgn.com/web-drakkar.html to play the wonderful Web
version of the Kingdom of Drakkar free!!!  No strings attached.
